│                                                                                                                              │
│ So, `I` is `Instruction*`. My code is `dyn_cast<StoreInst>(&I)`. This is taking the address of a pointer, resulting in       │
│ `Instruction**`, which is exactly what the compiler is complaining about.                                                    │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The fix is simple: I must not take the address of `I`. The line should be `if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(I))`.          │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ I will now apply this final correction.                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                      │
│ sed -i 's/dyn_cast<StoreInst>(&I)/dyn_cast<StoreInst>(I)/' llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstructionCombining.cpp          │
│ ```                                                                                                                          │
